{
  "stem": "8775.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And she-- the only conversation was in German.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And so was the conversation with my relatives, in German.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And this-- therefore, when we came to the ghetto and the concentration camps, I was somewhat advantageous to learn-- to know the language.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "My mother was educated also in Germany, and she was absolutely fluent, what they used to call Hochdeutsche.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "She spoke the high German language.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And my father spoke fluent German as well.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "My mother, she, she loved her home.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "She loved to do baking.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Every time for snacks, there was always baked goods, pastry, or something around the house.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And she was fairly religious.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "My father was always kidding my mother that she should have been a rebbetzin, the wife of a rabbi, because she was the last one to, to leave the temple.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And she had to wait until the last prayer was said or the last song was sung, and she would be closing the temple.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So that was pretty much my upbringing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "My father practiced law, as I said.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "In Szolnok there were two courts, something similar to what we have here, a municipal and a Superior Court.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But in Budapest, they also had two courts, the Supreme Court, and there was like, one in between.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And on many occasions, he had to travel up to Budapest to, to try cases in front of those courts.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And on some of these occasions, of course, he took us along, my mother and myself.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And those were very happy times, when we went to hear, like, opera, as I said, in, in Budapest, Margaret Island, there was an open-air amphitheater, where we got tickets and we heard the, the opera.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And he took us to, to other theaters, not only opera, but other theaters as well.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
